over the last couple of weeks, the world has been swarmed with images and videos coming from india. they tell the story of intense devastation. and officials say india is far from the peak of this second wave. this is the worst covid outbreak in the world. it’s shattered the previous global daily highs for cases and deaths. we see people having to fend for themselves. if you’ve been on twitter or ig you’ve seen posting desperate pleas for oxygen, medicine and hospital beds. it is chaotic and heartbreaking. i think all of us in the diaspora have been terrified of what’s happening back home. everyones got relatives impacted. many have sadly died.

behind this, is a host of issues. we’re joined by @ranaayyub who’s done tremendous work in reporting on the crisis. rana ayyub is one of the most important journalists of our time. her investigative work over the last decade has left me in awe and absolutely speechless. it is an honour and a privilege to once again have rana with us today.

